gw.api.dashboard

Class DashboardTreeGroupInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.admin.TreeGroupInfo
      • gw.api.dashboard.DashboardTreeGroupInfo

  • public class DashboardTreeGroupInfo
extends TreeGroupInfo
    Used to represent a node in the tree view that displays groups and users on the dashboard pages. This class is necessary because most nodes in the tree correspond to a single group but in one special case we need a node that represents a "pseudo group" (usually called "My Groups") which contains all the groups supervised or managed by the current user. This class provides a consistent interface for both a normal group and the special "My Groups" case.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DashboardTreeGroupInfo

        public DashboardTreeGroupInfo(Group group)
        Creates an object that gets information about a group, for use in a dashboard page. The main purpose of the object is to handle the special pseudo group "My Groups". For users who do not have permission to see the root of the group tree "My Groups" is a pseudo group which contains all the top level groups visible to the user. The DashboardTreeGroupInfo object hides the difference between this pseudo group and real groups by implementing the operations common to both - for example getSubGroups.
        Parameters:
        group - the group to view or null to get a view of the "root" group (either the actual root group or "My Groups", depending on the user)

    • Method Detail

      • getAllGroups

        public java.util.List<Group> getAllGroups()
        If the current group isn't null, add it to the array of subGroups and return that as the result. Otherwise, just return subgroups.
